<p>Following on from <a href="http://rolandtanglao.com/2016/12/20/p1-boris-mann-urls-stanley-park-2005-ar-mr-2016/">yesterday’s post about AR and MR</a>, there was a twitter convo about the difference between Augmented and Mixed Reality (AR versus MR) and <a href="https://twitter.com/bmann/status/811711125486116864">here’s what Boris tweeted</a>:</p>

<blockquote>

@CurtisDuggan in MR, the system “sees” reality &amp; can adjust virtual items. In AR, virtual items are painted on top of reality.

</blockquote>
